.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
\fBMuSig2SecNonce\fP encapsulates a secret nonce in use in a MuSig2 signing session\&. Since this nonce persists outside of libsecp256k1 signing code, we must handle its construction and destruction ourselves\&. The secret nonce must be kept a secret, otherwise the private key may be leaked\&. As such, it needs to be treated in the same way that CKeys are treated\&. So this class handles the secure allocation of the \fBsecp256k1_musig_secnonce\fP object that libsecp256k1 uses, and only gives out references to this object to avoid any possibility of copies being made\&. Furthermore, objects of this class are not copyable to avoid nonce reuse\&. 
